  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="NTM1.10">
<l>karuppuvil malarkkaṇaik kāmavēḷaik kaḻaliṇai paṇintaṅkōr kariyalaṟa</l>
<l>maruppiṉai yocittuppuḷ vāypiḷanta maṇivaṇṇaṟ keṉṉai vakuttiṭeṉṟu</l>
<l>poruppaṉṉa māṭampo lintutōṉṟum putuvaiyar kōṉviṭṭu cittaṉkōtai</l>
<l>viruppuṭai yiṉṟamiḻ mālaivallār viṇṇavar kōṉaṭi naṇṇuvarē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Those who are capable [of mastering] the sweet garland</l>
<l rend="indent">	desired by Kōtai, [daughter of] Visnucitta, the chief of Putuvai, where</l>
<l rend="indent">mountain-like mansions appear shining,</l>
<l rend="indent">saying, ‘Assign me to the gem-hued [Lord], who, breaking the tusk of an elephant</l>
<l rend="indent">so that [it] bellowed there, split open the beak of the bird!’</l>
<l rend="indent">having made obeisance to the pair of feet of lord Kāma, who has a sugarcane</l>
<l rend="indent">bow [and] flower arrows,</l>
<l>will reach the feet of the King of the celestials.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
